under a different one.

580
01:05:53,058 --> 01:05:57,102
Well, l tell you, l don't even much bother
with guests registering any more.

581
01:05:57,187 --> 01:05:59,855
You know, one by one,
you drop the formalities.

582
01:05:59,939 --> 01:06:02,316
l shouldn't even bother
changing the sheets,

583
01:06:02,400 --> 01:06:04,652
but old habits die hard.

584
01:06:05,445 --> 01:06:06,528
Which reminds me...

585
01:06:07,530 --> 01:06:10,407
-What's that?
-lt's the light. The sign.

586
01:06:10,867 --> 01:06:13,661
We had a couple last week,
said if the thing hadn't been on,

587
01:06:13,745 --> 01:06:15,829
they would've thought
this was an old, deserted...

588
01:06:15,914 --> 01:06:18,207
Well, you see, that's exactly my point.

589
01:06:18,291 --> 01:06:20,167
You said that nobody'd been here
for a couple weeks,

590
01:06:20,251 --> 01:06:23,045
and there's a couple came by
and didn't know that you were open.

591
01:06:23,129 --> 01:06:24,129
Yeah.

592
01:06:24,631 --> 01:06:26,507
Well, as you say, old habits die hard.

593
01:06:26,591 --> 01:06:29,510
lt's possible, this girl could've registered
under another name.

594
01:06:29,594 --> 01:06:31,220
Do you mind if l look at your book?

595
01:06:31,304 --> 01:06:33,263
-No.
-Thank you.

596
01:06:36,351 --> 01:06:37,518
All right.

597
01:06:37,602 --> 01:06:39,853
l'll get the date somewhere.

598
01:06:41,314 --> 01:06:42,940
See, there's nobody.

599
01:06:43,024 --> 01:06:46,777
Let's see now, l have a sample of her
handwriting here.

600
01:06:48,613 --> 01:06:49,905
Oh, yes.

601
01:06:50,824 --> 01:06:52,241
Here we are.

602
01:06:52,575 --> 01:06:55,536
Marie Samuels. That's an interesting alias.

603
01:06:56,579 --> 01:06:58,997
-ls that her?
-Yeah. Yeah, l think so.

604
01:06:59,082 --> 01:07:01,083
Marie, Marion.

605
01:07:01,167 --> 01:07:03,836
Samuels. Her boyfriend's name is Sam.

606
01:07:03,920 --> 01:07:04,920
Mmm-hmm.

607
01:07:05,338 --> 01:07:07,840
Was she in disguise, by any chance?

608
01:07:09,384 --> 01:07:12,761
-Wanna check the picture again?
-Look, l wasn't lying to you, Mr...

609
01:07:12,846 --> 01:07:14,888
Oh, l know that. l know you wouldn't lie.

610
01:07:14,973 --> 01:07:16,849
You know, it's tough keeping track
of the time around here.

611
01:07:16,933 --> 01:07:18,684
Oh, l know, l know.

612
01:07:19,477 --> 01:07:21,061
Oh, yeah.

613
01:07:21,146 --> 01:07:23,313
Well, it was raining

614
01:07:24,607 --> 01:07:26,358
and her hair was all wet.

615
01:07:26,443 --> 01:07:29,153
l tell you, it's not really
a very good picture of her either.

616
01:07:29,237 --> 01:07:30,863
No, l guess not.

617
01:07:30,947 --> 01:07:32,448
Tell me all about her.

618
01:07:32,532 --> 01:07:33,824
Well,

619
01:07:34,284 --> 01:07:38,537
she arrived rather late one night,
and she went straight to sleep

620
01:07:38,621 --> 01:07:41,248
and left early the next morning.

621
01:07:41,332 --> 01:07:44,460
-How early?
-Oh, very early.

622
01:07:44,544 --> 01:07:47,755
Mmm-hmm. Which morning was that?

623
01:07:47,839 --> 01:07:49,089
The...

624
01:07:52,010 --> 01:07:54,511
-The next morning. Sunday.
-l see.

625
01:07:55,472 --> 01:07:57,514
-Did anyone meet her here?
-No.

626
01:07:57,599 --> 01:08:00,517
-Did she arrive with anyone?
-No.

627
01:08:00,977 --> 01:08:03,103
-Did she make any phone calls or...
-No.

628
01:08:03,188 --> 01:08:04,521
Locally?

629
01:08:05,440 --> 01:08:07,858
Did you spend the night with her?

630
01:08:08,109 --> 01:08:09,359
No.

631
01:08:09,444 --> 01:08:13,238
Well then, how would you know
that she didn't make any phone calls?

632
01:08:14,657 --> 01:08:15,866
(STAMMERlNG)

633
01:08:16,951 --> 01:08:18,911
Well, she was very tired and...

634
01:08:18,995 --> 01:08:22,289
See, now l'm starting to remember.

635
01:08:22,373 --> 01:08:23,957
l'm making a mental picture of it in my mind.

636
01:08:24,042 --> 01:08:25,918
You know, if you make a mental
picturisation of something...

637
01:08:26,002 --> 01:08:28,629
That's right. That's right. Take your time.

638
01:08:28,713 --> 01:08:31,048
She was... She was sitting back there...

639
01:08:31,132 --> 01:08:34,051
No, no, she was standing back there
with a sandwich in her hand

640
01:08:34,135 --> 01:08:35,803
and she said she had to go to sleep early

641
01:08:35,887 --> 01:08:40,891
because she had a long drive ahead of her.

642
01:08:41,518 --> 01:08:43,477
-Back where?
-Back where she came from.

643
01:08:43,561 --> 01:08:46,355
No, you said before that she was
sitting back there... Standing back there...

644
01:08:46,439 --> 01:08:48,899
Yes, back in my parlour there.

645
01:08:48,983 --> 01:08:51,109
She was very hungry
and l made her a sandwich

646
01:08:51,194 --> 01:08:56,615
and then she said that she was tired
and she had to go right to bed.

647
01:08:56,699 --> 01:08:58,867
l see. How did she pay you?

648
01:08:58,952 --> 01:09:00,285
-Cash? Cheque?
-Cash.

649
01:09:00,370 --> 01:09:01,703
Cash, huh?

650
01:09:02,789 --> 01:09:06,458
-And after she left, she didn't come back?
-Well, why should she?

651
01:09:06,543 --> 01:09:07,543
Yeah.

652
01:09:09,295 --> 01:09:10,587
(CLEARS THROAT)

653
01:09:12,173 --> 01:09:15,259
Well, Mr Arbogast, l guess that's about it.

654
01:09:16,010 --> 01:09:18,595
l've got some work to do, if you don't mind.

655
01:09:18,680 --> 01:09:20,681
Well, to tell you the truth, l do mind.

656
01:09:20,765 --> 01:09:24,893
You see, if it doesn't jell, it isn't aspic,
and this ain't jelling.

657
01:09:24,978 --> 01:09:28,063
lt's not coming together.
Something's missing.

658
01:09:28,523 --> 01:09:31,984
Well, l don't know
what you could expect me to know.

659
01:09:32,068 --> 01:09:33,527
People just come and go, you know.

660
01:09:33,611 --> 01:09:37,239
-That's right. She isn't still here, is she?
-No.

661
01:09:39,284 --> 01:09:42,244
lf l wanted to check the cabins,
all 1 2 of them,

662
01:09:42,328 --> 01:09:43,579
l'd need a warrant, wouldn't l?

663
01:09:43,663 --> 01:09:46,540
Listen, if you don't believe me, come on
with me. You can help me change beds.

664
01:09:46,624 --> 01:09:49,209
-Okay?
-No, thanks.

665
01:10:06,978 --> 01:10:08,645
Change your mind?

666
01:10:11,900 --> 01:10:15,986
You know, l... l think l must have one
of those faces you just can't help believing.

667
01:10:16,070 --> 01:10:17,863
-ls anyone at home?
-No.

668
01:10:17,947 --> 01:10:20,240
Oh? There's somebody
sitting up in the window.

669
01:10:20,325 --> 01:10:22,701
-No, no, there isn't.
-Sure, go ahead. Take a look.

670
01:10:22,785 --> 01:10:24,745
Oh, that must be my mother.

671
01:10:24,829 --> 01:10:27,289
She's an invalid.

672
01:10:27,373 --> 01:10:29,374
lt's practically like living alone.

673
01:10:29,459 --> 01:10:30,959
Oh, l see.

674
01:10:32,170 --> 01:10:36,590
Now, if this girl, Marion Crane, were here,
you wouldn't be hiding her, would you?

675
01:10:36,674 --> 01:10:39,009
-No.
-Not even if she paid you well?

676
01:10:39,093 --> 01:10:40,177
No.

677
01:10:40,845 --> 01:10:45,933
Let's just say, just for the sake of argument,
that she wanted you to gallantly protect her.

678
01:10:46,017 --> 01:10:47,893
You'd know that you were being used.

679
01:10:47,977 --> 01:10:49,269
You wouldn't be made a fool of, would you?

680
01:10:49,354 --> 01:10:50,938
-But l'm not a fool.
-Well, l...

681
01:10:51,022 --> 01:10:54,066
And l'm not capable of being fooled,
not even by a woman.

682
01:10:54,150 --> 01:10:56,568
-Well, this is not a slur on your manhood.
-Let's put it this way.

683
01:10:56,653 --> 01:11:00,530
She might have fooled me,
but she didn't fool my mother.

684
01:11:00,615 --> 01:11:02,532
Well, then your mother met her.
Could l talk to your mother?

685
01:11:02,617 --> 01:11:05,285
No. As l told you, she's confined.

686
01:11:05,370 --> 01:11:06,620
Yes, but just for a few minutes. That's all.

687
01:11:06,704 --> 01:11:08,789
There might be some hint
that you missed out on.

688
01:11:08,873 --> 01:11:11,208
You know, sick old women
are usually pretty sharp.

689
01:11:11,292 --> 01:11:14,962
-Mr Arbogast... l think l've...
-Just for a moment. l wouldn't disturb her.

690
01:11:15,046 --> 01:11:17,881
-l think l've talked to you all l want to.
-Yes, but just for...

691
01:11:17,966 --> 01:11:20,258
l think it'd be much better if you left now.
Thanks.

692
01:11:21,219 --> 01:11:23,095
Well, all right.

693
01:11:23,846 --> 01:11:27,140
You sure would save me a lot of leg work
if you'd let me talk to her.

694
01:11:27,225 --> 01:11:28,642
-Would l need a warrant for that, too?
-Sure.

695
01:11:28,726 --> 01:11:29,726
Uh-huh.

696
01:11:30,687 --> 01:11:32,896
All right. Thanks anyway.

697
01:11:43,408 --> 01:11:44,700
(STARTS ENGlNE)

698
01:11:51,040 --> 01:11:52,624
(CAR PULLS AWAY)

699
01:12:27,076 --> 01:12:30,162
Hello, Loomis. This is Arbogast.
ls Lila there?

700
01:12:30,538 --> 01:12:32,706
Okay. Let me talk to her, please.

701
01:12:34,042 --> 01:12:35,500
Hello, Lila.

702
01:12:36,169 --> 01:12:38,962
Lila, listen. Marion was up here.

703
01:12:39,964 --> 01:12:42,674
Yes, she spent last Saturday night
at the Bates Motel.

704
01:12:42,759 --> 01:12:44,551
lt's right out here on the old highway.

705
01:12:44,635 --> 01:12:48,096
l even know what cabin she was in.
lt was number one.

706
01:12:48,598 --> 01:12:52,893
Well, this young fella that runs the place
said that she just spent the night,

707
01:12:52,977 --> 01:12:55,479
left the next day and that was it.

708
01:12:57,982 --> 01:12:59,649
No, not exactly.

709
01:13:00,818 --> 01:13:05,238
Well, l did question him, believe me,
but l think l got all there was to get.

710
01:13:05,323 --> 01:13:08,492
l'll just have to pick up the pieces from here.

711
01:13:08,951 --> 01:13:12,537
Well, l tell you,
l don't feel entirely satisfied...

712
01:13:12,622 --> 01:13:14,956
See, this boy had a sick old mother.

713
01:13:15,041 --> 01:13:17,959
l think she saw Marion and talked to her.

714
01:13:18,044 --> 01:13:21,296
No. No, unfortunately,
he wouldn't let me see her.

715
01:13:21,714 --> 01:13:25,509
Well, l was,
but l think l'll go back to the motel first.

716
01:13:26,511 --> 01:13:30,055
No, you stay there with Loomis.
l'll be back in about an hour.

717
01:13:30,139 --> 01:13:32,224
All right, fine. Listen, l...

718
01:13:32,308 --> 01:13:34,768
You'll be happy to know what l think.

719
01:13:34,852 --> 01:13:38,855
l think our friend Sam Loomis
didn't know that Marion was here.

720
01:13:40,566 --> 01:13:43,735
